EDIT: Problem resolved. Had to change lines:
   
     int x = stack.firstElement().getKey();   
     int y = stack.firstElement().getValue();

into:
   

     int x = stack.peek().getKey();   
     int y = stack.peek().getValue();

Turns out method .firstElement() doesn&#39;t give you first element (the one on top of the stack) but the one that was first inserted (always the same object) so in the end all the operation were performed on one, single element and not multiple ones.

